Text.Value: Don't worry. I have no interest in a devil's deal.
- but that's not a lesson that needs repeating, I wager.

Well, there's the matter of Duke Stelmane and the Knights of the Shield.
Thousands were sacrificed, and the servant become lord. I am sure you're quite pleased with yourself.
Thousands were sacrificed, and the servant become lord. I am sure Astarion's quite pleased with himself.
I'd love nothing more than to see her grind that wretch into bonedust.
He's not just any githyanki. He's a prince, the son of Great Mother Gith.

Damned goblins. Monsters, every last one - the kind I was culling from Sword Coast hamlets just a tenday ago.
Were I to choose, I'd break the prince free. Better to entrust our fates to him before making an unneeded sacrifice - or entrusting Orpheus' power to the illithid.
Too dangerous, even, for Mystra. But I would sooner trust it with a god than a man.
I can't pretend I have the answer. But I know the illithid's right about one thing:
Minsc, the great ranger. He's alive - and infected? Hells. We need to act.
You slurped that thing up like a horse with a carrot.
Githyanki are impressive - cold as ice, when they're not blazing hot. I wager Lae'zel's no exception.
I see the hunger in your eyes, and I see how it worries you.
Gods - have we really cut down the Great Ranger Minsc? A nightmare that can never be erased from my memory.
Erm - as glad as I am to have the hammer, I'm not so sure a devil's deal was the way to go here.
The faith that matters is that which you hold in yourself, in the ones that most matter to you.

Leave.
Death is staring you down. And so you want these last moments to count for something.

Today, a sacrifice must be made. I trust in you to lead us down the right path.

Karlach, I'm so sorry.

- goodness, my palms are all sweaty. It's just that - you were always my hero.
It holds our fates in its talons. Until the Absolute falls, there's no getting rid of it.
Bhaal's chosen has been bled. May her torment be tenfold of that which she inflicted.
A veritable angel, chained and tortured for centuries. To think she was so close to freedom.
The gith knight is as merciless as the dragon he rides. That we still have our heads is nothing short of a miracle.
Consume all the magic artefacts you need to keep that bomb of yours from exploding.
Devils. Ever do they try to sway the mind with the dangling temptations.
Wyll fights for good, does he not? It is not for Minsc or you to judge a hero like the Blade of Frontiers.
The source of Gortash's Watchers. If I could get over my disgust, I might be impressed.
Leave.
Refuse him like you refused Mizora? Only, you didn't, did you?
Good idea.
Such soothing light here, as if Selûne herself was caressing my skin.
Dammit all, we've got to get Lae'zel back. If that means killing Gortash, nothing would give me greater pleasure.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 148 - Defeating Raphael in the HoH

I don't want to talk about it.
Ah yes - the wayward prince, locked away by the queen who would wield his power.
An anti-lantern that radiates darkness and not light? Clever idea. Unnerving, too.

But you said it anyway, to your immense credit. You're choosing truth, you're choosing freedom - for you, for Orpheus, for your people.

Too dangerous, even, for Mystra. But I would sooner trust it with a god than with Gale.
Incredible to be back. My home, my city.
I hope that's the end of this silly quarrel. They'll have no energy for battling our enemies if Lae'zel and Shadowheart are too busy squabbling among themselves.

So you say.
Listen - I might invoke the Triad from time to time, appeal to Helm. But I'm no man of faith. Not like Gale.
An old fairy tale my father read to me. The kind with a hero, a villain, and a moral.

Really.

Hold close to the light, and keep the shadows at bay.
Let's talk about something else.

I made a mistake. This is your chance to learn from it.

Welcome to the Lower City, where Baldur's Gate truly comes alive.
When the Absolute falls, I wager our alliance falls with it.
Astarion has a certain swagger, don't you find? An interesting fellow. Nice hair, to boot.
Death is staring you down. And so you want these last moments to count for something.
Death is staring her down. And she want these last moments to count for something.
Defile Vlaakith's name, and even a gith knight can't avoid the wrath of the mighty Lae'zel.

The Plane of Shadow. My tutor called it a dark mirror held up to our own plane of existence, a perversion of all we hold dear.
To think this crèche was nestled in the valley, a day's trot away.
You should tell your hero how you exchanged your father's life for your soul.

EditorData.logicalname: Wyll pacted, gave up his father

Text.Value: Our very own vampire's the missing pawn in his master's deadly game.

The faith that matters is that which you hold in yourself, in the ones that most matter to you.

'The Devil with the Silver Tongue.'

Karlach never ceases to amaze me.

Lae'zel is a powderkeg - and Shadowheart was the spark.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 161 - Shar punished SH after sparing NS

Let's change the subject.

We should have as little to do with these tadpoles as we can.

Three: The mind flayer's been siphoning a githyanki prisoner's powers to shield us from the Absolute's voice.
The Gur was a monster hunter, not so different from me - and we slayed him on your behalf.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 151 - Defeated the Gur Hunters with Vampire Lord Astarion (Avatar only)

Two: It's been appearing as someone else in our dreams, cajoling us to embrace our new illithid talents.
Ah - what a relief to have you back with us. Who doesn't enjoy a bit of pomp with their circumstance?
Who better to warn you of the danger ahead?

Killing Astarion was the right thing to do. I have to believe that.

This crown seems too powerful and dangerous an object for mere mortals to possess.
This crown seems too powerful and dangerous an object for mere mortals to possess, Gale.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 54 - Killed Gortash (only if Ravengard is alive to avoid conflict elsewhere)

Text.Value: Interesting, coming from someone who's already been ensnared by a devil.
Tell Wyll about the orb in your chest, and how it came to be there.
Vampire spawn. One's proven enough, let alone a horde of them.
Really?
I spent years swatting away my fears and doubts of my infernal fate - but I eventually made my peace. I had to.
I thought she was exaggerating. And I was wrong.
The seed of tyranny begins with the want for power. Nurture it, let it grow, and we become the very despots we once despised.
Ah, yes - Gith's only son, locked away in his astral prison for defying Vlaakith.
Tell Wyll the story of your orb. Leave nothing out.
The magic in those objects helps maintain my spellcasting talents.
Careful who you point your blade at next. We can afford no more unrest among us, not if we're to survive long enough to rid ourselves of these worms.
If she points a blade at one of us again, don't hesitate to strike. We can afford no more unrest among us, not if we're to survive long enough to rid ourselves of these worms.
By the gone gods. It isn't the blood you've spilled or the lives you've snuffed out that horrify me most.
But I'm not convinced the githyanki prince wouldn't smash us to pieces given the chance.
Your truth is finally dawning, Shadowheart. You can follow its light - or you can retreat back into dusk.
The truth is finally dawning. Shadowheart can follow its light - or she can retreat back into dusk.
What would your 'hero' think about how you killed Karlach, an innocent tiefling?
Very well. If it's mind games these parasites wish to play, we'll play. And we'll win.
Come. We have a Netherbrain to tear up.
Understandable. Every tale was more sensational than the last. With a narrator so unreliable, how do we tell fact from fiction?
Seems you're the missing pawn in your master's deadly game.
Our very own vampire's the missing pawn in his master's deadly game.
Minsc is being tricked. By the Hells, we've got to rip him away from that shapeshifter.
And yet... I can't help recall the words of my father. 'The best plan is the one that works.'
I don't know what drives a man to consider his own death, among countless others, to be an appropriate exchange for his goddess' forgiveness.
My head throbs with every step. The closer the brain, the louder its call.
And then take more still.
Insert the artefact into the planecaster. I don't know about you, but I'm ready to see who - or what - is inside it.
You never cease to amaze me.
Karlach never ceases to amaze me.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 174 - Emperor gave options Karlach offer

Text.Value: Her mind will be wiped, and Viconia will remake her in whatever image she desires.
Hunt the monsters of the Sword Coast, protect the people - that was my promise.
You will too, Karlach. I know it.
We know he keeps it in the House of Hope. If we can find a diabolist, they could help us make our way in.
Do not trust a devil. Is that plain enough?
Not that I'm one to question someone's meal preferences, but something tells me this is more than a dietary quirk.
I'm no hero. But I've dedicated my life to keeping the Sword Coast safe from the monsters that roam it.
Get your gear in order and rest up. We've got an undead elf to go recue.
Orin's game is abduction, is it? Well - we can't stand idly by. We've got an ally to rescue.
Take a single step towards him, and he'll dog you the whole journey.
If someone must assimilate Orpheus, I'd sooner trust you with the power than the illithid...
Assimilate Orpheus for yourself, and you become illithid. The Emperor does it, and it claims the prince's power for himself.
Taken from the light to be raised in darkness.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 162 - Shadowheart learned the truth about her past from Nightsong

Text.Value: We can break him free. He might give us options we hadn't thought of, opened doors that we thought were closed.
You're glowing with magic. Mystra must be mighty happy right about now.
Gale's glowing with magic. Mystra must be mighty happy right about now.
I have seen the ravages visited on Toril by the gods, Gale. Even the ones we so naively call 'good'.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 179 - Avatar Gale turned his back on Mystra

Text.Value: You did what was right, knowing you stood to suffer for it. In so doing, you proved what it means to be a hero.
Shadowheart did what was right, knowing she stood to suffer for it. In so doing, she proved what it means to be a hero.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 165 - Shadowheart freed her parents after abandoning Shar at the last minute in Act 3

Text.Value: But this is your decision to make. Wherever you lead, I will follow.
Thousands were sacrificed, and the servant become lord. I am sure Astarion's quite pleased with himself.
But if assimilation is your choice, I won't stop you. I never would.
Well - I'll cross this place off our list off possible holiday destinations.
Who among us hasn't wondered what it would be like to live forever?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 156 - Player asked Jaheira about the scroll they found in her home - Jaheira explained the Timeless Body Ritual, but burned the scroll in a passing of the torch to the player.

Text.Value: You never cease to amaze me.
I fear we have no choice. What I ask is unreasonable by every standard. It sickens me to think, let alone say, but -
Maybe you should avoid items laced with dark magic. 'You are what you eat', as the old adage goes.
Maybe Gale should avoid items laced with dark magic. 'You are what you eat', as the old adage goes.
The seat of the Iron Throne was razed a century ago - or so it was said.
Mystra wants to meet Gale? Impressive. The only thing a god's ever offered me is a cold shoulder.
Mystra wants to meet Gale? Impressive. The only thing a god's ever offered me is a cold shoulder.
You'd become a mind flayer - but you'd lead us to a sure victory. It's what you do.
*Your parasite tingles. Minsc knows that Wyll speaks true.*
Just some food for thought.
Hm - the place is remarkably well-kept, as underground lairs go.
A shame my first brush with the famed Elminster couldn't be a tad more... optimistic.
Lae'zel's suspicion and your guile made for a lethal combination. I fear for our fellowship, if trust is in such short supply.
Lae'zel's suspicion and Shadowheart's guile made for a lethal combination. I fear for our fellowship, if trust is in such short supply.
He's not just any githyanki, but a prince who opposed the githyanki queen.
The farmer's dearest fruit, naturally, was no apple nor peach, but his beloved daughter.
Ah - you drank of the goblet of godhood. Not even a dwarf could distil a liquor more addictive.
There's a schism growing among your people, Lae'zel. And you just took one step towards choosing a side.
There's a schism growing among your people. And Lae'zel just took one step towards choosing a side.
There's a schism growing among the githyanki people. And Lae'zel just took one step towards choosing a side.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 140 - Voss came, Lae'zel agreed to meet him

Text.Value: But we've got to tread carefully. I won't risk my father's life to take Gortash's.

EditorData.logicalname: Ravengard not dead or in IRN yet

Text.Value: I trust that's the end of this silly quarrel? We'll have no energy for battling our enemies if we're too busy squabbling among ourselves.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 118 - Lae'zel and SH fought - peaceful outcome
